for(initialize; termination; increment or decrement) 


Initialize - initialize the loop and executed once
Termination - For loop won't exit till the 'termination' is set to false
Increment - Adds to the loop

Example: 

for(int i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
	System.out.println(i);
}


Example with 'break':

int count = 0;    // make sure that the variable is placed outside of the FOR loop.

for (int i = 10; i < 50; i++) {
	if(isPrime(i)) {
	System.out.println(i);
	count++;
	}
	if (count == 3) {
		System.out.println("exiting the loop");
		break;
	}
}
